OL,3,CPlymouth City Council's #15million
OL,4,Cplan to ease the housing crisis
OL,6,F"We have listened to the feedback from
OL,7,Fresidents and in our recent budget
OL,8,Fconsultation, people recognised that
OL,9,Fwe all have a duty to ensure that the
OL,10,Fmost vulnerable ` our children, older
OL,11,Fpeople or those who are homeless ` are
OL,12,Fprotected. Unfortunately, those are
OL,13,Fthe exact areas we are seeing the most
OL,14,Ffinancial pressure.
OL,16,F"What I can promise is that whilst we
OL,17,Fall tighten our belts, we will
OL,18,Fcontinue to lobby hard for what is
OL,19,Fright and fair for Plymouth and most
OL,20,Fimportantly we are ambitious. We will
OL,21,Fstrive to put the city on the map."
